title: Number of CityKey cards issued, pre 2021

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

records sufficient to show the number of CityKey cards issued per month between January 2018 and December 2020.

Thank you so much for your response to my previous FOIA request for number of CityKey cards issued starting in 2021.  I was able to use that to make this visualisation showing how much CityCard issuances has increased in the past few years. https://observablehq.com/@fgregg/chicago-citykeys-issued

I'd like to get a few more earlier years of data to get a clearer baseline. Please provide me the data in the same format as the previous request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Forest Gregg

title: Communication with WSAC regarding indigent defense suit against the state of Washington

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Communication with WSAC regarding indigent defense suit against the state of Washington
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any emails to/from Dow Constantine, Shannon Braddock, Dwight Dively, April Putney, or Chase Gallagher from/to Eric Johnson, Mike Hoover, Mary Kuney, Lisa Janicki, Rob Coffman, or anyone else with an @wsac.org email address mentioning "public defense" or "indigent defense" from the last 3 months.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kevin Moore
